{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T05:25:11.222Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777181110955_0","status":"success","output":"commit b11e9cdb52c2e35d8545eab3f6173d0ebcb71ed9 (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 22:24:13 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(sampler): add sw_sampler granular SynthDef [T-032@20260425T183959Z]\n    \n    The granular memory voice for the signature quintet. GrainBuf-based\n    buffer scrub with grain_size_ms / density / position / position_rate /\n    pitch transpose+jitter / Env.asr (gate, doneAction:2) and a parallel\n    fx_send into bus 16 alongside the dry write to out_bus.\n    \n    - my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd — SynthDef source\n    - my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd — runtime test on cypherclaw:\n      compile, render 2 s from a known sine buffer, assert non-silence and\n      a spectral peak near the probe frequency, and verify gate=0 release\n      tail decay\n    - tests/test_sw_sampler.py — static SCD source checks (args, defaults,\n      range clips, signal chain, fx-send routing) so regressions surface in\n      CI without sclang\n\ndiff --git a/my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd b/my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..786efe7\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd\n@@ -0,0 +1,175 @@\n+// test_sw_sampler.scd — SC-side smoke test for the sw_sampler granular voice.\n+//\n+// Runs on cypherclaw (where sclang/scsynth are installed). Verifies:\n+//   (a) The SynthDef source compiles and the .scsyndef is written.\n+//   (b) Rendering 2 seconds from a known sine buffer produces non-silence.\n+//   (c) The output spectrum has a dominant peak near the sine's frequency\n+//       (granular reproduction of pitched material preserves pitch class).\n+//   (d) Setting gate=0 triggers a release tail (audible after gate close,\n+//       then decays toward silence within `release_sec`).\n+//\n+// Usage (from the my-claw repo root):\n+//   sclang my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd\n+//\n+// Exit codes / output:\n+//   - All assertions print \"PASS …\" lines on success.\n+//   - Any failure prints \"FAIL …\" with diagnostics; non-zero exit via 1.exit.\n+\n+(\n+~sampleRate     = 48000;\n+~renderDur      = 2.0;\n+~probeFreqHz    = 440.0;\n+~peakTolHz      = 8.0;\n+~releaseSec     = 0.25;\n+~gateCloseAt    = 1.0;\n+~sourcePath     = \"my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd\";\n+~defPath        = \"my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler.scsyndef\";\n+\n+~assert = { |cond, label|\n+    if (cond) {\n+        (\"PASS \" ++ label).postln;\n+    } {\n+        (\"FAIL \" ++ label).postln;\n+        1.exit;\n+    };\n+};\n+\n+~windowRms = { |arr, startSec, endSec|\n+    var start = (startSec * ~sampleRate).asInteger.clip(0, arr.size - 1);\n+    var stop  = (endSec   * ~sampleRate).asInteger.clip(start + 1, arr.size);\n+    var window = arr.copyRange(start, stop - 1);\n+    (((window * window).sum) / window.size.max(1)).sqrt;\n+};\n+\n+// --- (a) Compile the source SynthDef ------------------------------------\n+~sourcePath.load;\n+~assert.(SynthDescLib.global.at(\\sw_sampler).notNil,\n+    \"source SynthDef registered: \" ++ ~sourcePath);\n+~assert.(File.exists(~defPath), \"compiled scsyndef present: \" ++ ~defPath);\n+\n+s.waitForBoot {\n+    var runRender, runRelease;\n+\n+    // A short stereo recorder that captures whatever lands on `in_bus` so\n+    // we can post-process the audio offline.\n+    SynthDef(\\test_sampler_record, { |in = 0, buf = 0|\n+        RecordBuf.ar(In.ar(in, 2).sum * 0.5, buf, loop: 0, doneAction: 2);\n+    }).add;\n+\n+    s.sync;\n+\n+    runRender = { |gateCloseAt, onDone|\n+        fork {\n+            var probeBuf, recBuf, outBus, samplerSyn;\n+            var probeFrames = (~sampleRate * 1.0).asInteger;\n+            var sineWave;\n+\n+            // Allocate a 1-second mono sine buffer at ~probeFreqHz so the\n+            // grain cloud has known spectral content to reproduce.\n+            probeBuf = Buffer.alloc(s, probeFrames, 1);\n+            sineWave = Array.fill(probeFrames, { |i|\n+                (2pi * ~probeFreqHz * i / ~sampleRate).sin * 0.6;\n+            });\n+            probeBuf.loadCollection(sineWave);\n+\n+            outBus = Bus.audio(s, 2);\n+            recBuf = Buffer.alloc(s, (~sampleRate * ~renderDur).asInteger, 1);\n+            s.sync;\n+\n+            samplerSyn = Synth(\\sw_sampler, [\n+                \\bufnum,                    probeBuf.bufnum,\n+                \\amp,                       0.5,\n+                \\grain_size_ms,             80.0,\n+                \\density,                   12.0,\n+                \\position,                  0.0,\n+                \\position_rate,             0.5,\n+                \\pitch_transpose_semitones, 0.0,\n+                \\pitch_jitter_semitones,    0.0,\n+                \\attack_sec,                0.05,\n+                \\release_sec,               ~releaseSec,\n+                \\gate,                      1,\n+                \\out_bus,                   outBus.index,\n+                \\fx_send,                   0.0\n+            ]);\n+            Synth.after(samplerSyn, \\test_sampler_record,\n+                [\\in, outBus.index, \\buf, recBuf]);\n+\n+            if (gateCloseAt.notNil) {\n+                SystemClock.sched(gateCloseAt, {\n+                    samplerSyn.set(\\gate, 0);\n+                    nil;\n+                });\n+            };\n+\n+            (~renderDur + 0.2).wait;\n+            // Synth self-frees on doneAction:2 if gate was closed; otherwise\n+            // free explicitly so the test is deterministic.\n+            samplerSyn.free;\n+\n+            recBuf.loadToFloatArray(action: { |arr|\n+                recBuf.free;\n+                outBus.free;\n+                probeBuf.free;\n+                onDone.(arr);\n+            });\n+        };\n+    };\n+\n+    // (b)+(c): render the full 2 s with gate held open the entire time.\n+    runRender.(nil, { |arr|\n+        var peak, rms;\n+        var fftSize = 16384;\n+\n+        peak = arr.abs.maxItem;\n+        rms  = ((arr * arr).sum / arr.size).sqrt;\n+        ~assert.(peak > 0.001, \"non-silent grain cloud (peak > 1e-3)\");\n+        ~assert.(rms  > 1.0e-5, \"non-trivial RMS energy\");\n+\n+        // Spectral characteristic: dominant magnitude bin must sit close to\n+        // ~probeFreqHz, confirming the granular voice reproduces the\n+        // buffer's pitch rather than emitting broadband noise.\n+        block { |break|\n+            var sig = Signal.newClear(fftSize);\n+            var i = 0;\n+            var cosTbl, imag, spec, binHz, peakBin, peakHz;\n+\n+            while ({ (i < fftSize) and: { i < arr.size } }) {\n+                sig[i] = arr[i]; i = i + 1;\n+            };\n+            cosTbl = Signal.fftCosTable(fftSize);\n+            imag = Signal.newClear(fftSize);\n+            // Only inspect the lower half (Nyquist limit) for the peak bin.\n+            spec = sig.fft(imag, cosTbl).magnitude.copyRange(0, (fftSize / 2).asInteger - 1);\n+            binHz = ~sampleRate / fftSize;\n+            peakBin = spec.maxIndex;\n+            peakHz = peakBin * binHz;\n+\n+            ~assert.((peakHz - ~probeFreqHz).abs < ~peakTolHz,\n+                \"spectral peak near \" ++ ~probeFreqHz ++ \" Hz \"\n+                ++ \"(observed=\" ++ peakHz ++ \" Hz)\");\n+        };\n+\n+        // (d): same render, but close the gate mid-stream and confirm the\n+        // tail energy after release_sec has decayed below the in-flight RMS.\n+        runRender.(~gateCloseAt, { |arr2|\n+            var inFlight, postRelease;\n+\n+            inFlight    = ~windowRms.(arr2, 0.4, ~gateCloseAt);\n+            postRelease = ~windowRms.(arr2,\n+                ~gateCloseAt + ~releaseSec + 0.2,\n+                ~renderDur);\n+\n+            ~assert.(inFlight > 1.0e-4,\n+                \"in-flight RMS non-zero before gate close \"\n+                ++ \"(rms=\" ++ inFlight ++ \")\");\n+            ~assert.(postRelease < (inFlight * 0.25),\n+                \"post-release tail decays after gate=0 \"\n+                ++ \"(in_flight=\" ++ inFlight\n+                ++ \", post_release=\" ++ postRelease ++ \")\");\n+\n+            \"ALL TESTS PASSED\".postln;\n+            0.exit;\n+        });\n+    });\n+};\n+)\ndiff --git a/my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..b7c0a2e\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd\n@@ -0,0 +1,115 @@\n+// sw_sampler.scd — Source stub for the `sw_sampler` granular SynthDef.\n+//\n+// Companion source for `synthdefs/sw_sampler.scsyndef`. This is the memory\n+// voice of the signature quintet: a granular cloud over a buffer (live\n+// capture, self-quotation, or curated library sample) with a parallel\n+// send to the dedicated `sw_sampler_fx` bus (default stereo bus 16).\n+//\n+// Voice control surface (driven by `senseweave.sampler_dispatch.SamplerDispatcher`\n+// over OSC):\n+//\n+//     bufnum                      sample buffer to scrub (required)\n+//     amp                         linear output gain (post-envelope)\n+//     grain_size_ms               grain duration in milliseconds (20..200)\n+//     density                     grains per second (Impulse.kr trigger rate)\n+//     position                    initial buffer position, normalised 0..1\n+//     position_rate               scrub speed in normalised-pos / second\n+//                                 (0 = freeze on `position`, 1 = ~natural-time\n+//                                 scrub through the whole buffer per second)\n+//     pitch_transpose_semitones   constant transposition applied to grain rate\n+//     pitch_jitter_semitones      ±semitone jitter rolled per-grain (TRand)\n+//     attack_sec / release_sec    Env.asr envelope shape\n+//     gate                        sustained gate; gate=0 triggers release tail\n+//     out_bus                     dry destination (defaults to master 0)\n+//     fx_bus                      effects-bus destination (defaults to 16)\n+//     fx_send                     level of the parallel send into fx_bus\n+//\n+// Routing convention: the dry signal is written at full level to `out_bus`\n+// (master, channels 0/1 in our graph) and a parallel copy scaled by\n+// `fx_send` is written to `fx_bus` (16/17). `sw_sampler_fx` reads from 16\n+// and writes the processed tail back to 0, so master receives dry + wet.\n+//\n+// `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` self-frees the synth once the\n+// release tail completes after the caller flips `gate` to 0.\n+//\n+// Compile to synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler.scsyndef via .writeDefFile.\n+\n+(\n+SynthDef(\\sw_sampler, {\n+    | bufnum = 0,\n+      amp = 0.5,\n+      grain_size_ms = 80.0,\n+      density = 12.0,\n+      position = 0.0,\n+      position_rate = 0.0,\n+      pitch_transpose_semitones = 0.0,\n+      pitch_jitter_semitones = 0.1,\n+      attack_sec = 0.05,\n+      release_sec = 0.2,\n+      gate = 1.0,\n+      out_bus = 0,\n+      fx_bus = 16,\n+      fx_send = 0.4 |\n+\n+    var grainDur, dens, pos, posRate, transpose, jitter, atk, rel, fxAmt;\n+    var grainTrig, jitterSemis, rate, positionPhase, pan;\n+    var env, grain, sig, fxOut;\n+\n+    // Range-clip incoming controls to keep the granular engine numerically\n+    // stable. The acceptance ranges live here so OSC senders can push raw\n+    // values without crashing scsynth.\n+    grainDur  = grain_size_ms.clip(20.0, 200.0) * 0.001;\n+    dens      = density.clip(1.0, 200.0);\n+    pos       = position.clip(0.0, 1.0);\n+    posRate   = position_rate.clip(-8.0, 8.0);\n+    transpose = pitch_transpose_semitones.clip(-48.0, 48.0);\n+    jitter    = pitch_jitter_semitones.clip(0.0, 12.0);\n+    atk       = attack_sec.clip(0.001, 4.0);\n+    rel       = release_sec.clip(0.001, 8.0);\n+    fxAmt     = fx_send.clip(0.0, 1.0);\n+\n+    // Grain trigger train at the requested density (grains per second).\n+    grainTrig = Impulse.kr(dens);\n+\n+    // Per-grain pitch jitter (±jitter semitones) plus the constant\n+    // transpose, both folded into a single rate multiplier.\n+    jitterSemis = TRand.kr(jitter.neg, jitter, grainTrig);\n+    rate        = (transpose + jitterSemis).midiratio;\n+\n+    // Position scrub: normalised position advances at `posRate` units / sec.\n+    // Sweep.ar emits a continuous ramp so partial-grain interpolation stays\n+    // smooth; .wrap keeps the phase inside [0, 1] for GrainBuf.\n+    positionPhase = (pos + Sweep.ar(1, posRate)).wrap(0.0, 1.0);\n+\n+    // Mild stereo spread per grain; deterministic-feeling at low jitter.\n+    pan = TRand.kr(-0.6, 0.6, grainTrig);\n+\n+    // Stereo grain cloud. interp:2 = linear interp; envbufnum:-1 = built-in\n+    // Hanning grain envelope. maxGrains caps polyphony to keep CPU bounded.\n+    grain = GrainBuf.ar(\n+        numChannels: 2,\n+        trigger:     grainTrig,\n+        dur:         grainDur,\n+        sndbuf:      bufnum,\n+        rate:        rate,\n+        pos:         positionPhase,\n+        interp:      2,\n+        pan:         pan,\n+        envbufnum:   -1,\n+        maxGrains:   64\n+    );\n+\n+    // Attack / release envelope with sustain held by `gate`. doneAction:2\n+    // self-frees the synth once the release tail completes.\n+    env = EnvGen.kr(Env.asr(atk, 1.0, rel), gate, doneAction: 2);\n+\n+    sig = grain * env * amp;\n+\n+    // Parallel send architecture: dry at full level to out_bus, scaled\n+    // copy to the fx bus. Reducing fx_send does not pull down the dry.\n+    fxOut = sig * fxAmt;\n+\n+    Out.ar(out_bus, sig);\n+    Out.ar(fx_bus, fxOut);\n+}).writeDefFile(\"synthdefs/\");\n+)\ndiff --git a/tests/test_sw_sampler.py b/tests/test_sw_sampler.py\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..a4e9ae5\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/tests/test_sw_sampler.py\n@@ -0,0 +1,313 @@\n+\"\"\"Static tests for the sw_sampler granular SynthDef source.\n+\n+The compiled `.scsyndef` is produced by sclang on the cypherclaw deploy host;\n+this dev box has no SuperCollider toolchain. These tests therefore validate the\n+SCD source declaratively — name, argument list, default values, signal-chain\n+UGens, and bus conventions — so that regressions in the source surface in CI\n+even when sclang isn't available.\n+\n+The runtime behaviour assertions (non-silence, spectral peak near the probe\n+buffer's frequency, gate=0 release-tail decay) live in\n+`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` and run on cypherclaw.\n+\"\"\"\n+from __future__ import annotations\n+\n+import re\n+from pathlib import Path\n+\n+import pytest\n+\n+REPO_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent\n+SCD_PATH = (\n+    REPO_ROOT\n+    / \"my-claw\"\n+    / \"tools\"\n+    / \"senseweave\"\n+    / \"synthesis\"\n+    / \"sw_sampler.scd\"\n+)\n+SC_TEST_PATH = REPO_ROOT / \"my-claw\" / \"supercollider\" / \"test_sw_sampler.scd\"\n+\n+\n+@pytest.fixture(scope=\"module\")\n+def scd_source() -> str:\n+    assert SCD_PATH.is_file(), f\"sw_sampler.scd missing at {SCD_PATH}\"\n+    return SCD_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+\n+\n+def _arg_block(source: str) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Extract the SynthDef argument list (between the first `|...|` pair).\"\"\"\n+    match = re.search(r\"\\|\\s*([^|]+?)\\s*\\|\", source, flags=re.DOTALL)\n+    assert match, \"could not locate SynthDef argument list\"\n+    return match.group(1)\n+\n+\n+def _arg_default(arg_block: str, name: str) -> float:\n+    pattern = rf\"\\b{re.escape(name)}\\s*=\\s*(-?\\d+(?:\\.\\d+)?)\"\n+    match = re.search(pattern, arg_block)\n+    assert match, f\"argument {name!r} missing or has no default\"\n+    return float(match.group(1))\n+\n+\n+class TestSynthDefIdentity:\n+    def test_synthdef_name_is_sw_sampler(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(r\"SynthDef\\(\\\\sw_sampler\\b\", scd_source), (\n+            \"SynthDef must be named \\\\sw_sampler\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_writes_def_file_for_compilation(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert \".writeDefFile\" in scd_source, (\n+            \"SCD must invoke .writeDefFile so the .scsyndef can be compiled\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_writes_to_synthdefs_directory(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(r\"\\.writeDefFile\\(\\s*\\\"synthdefs/?\\\"\\s*\\)\",\n+                         scd_source), (\n+            \"compiled .scsyndef must land in synthesis/synthdefs/\"\n+        )\n+\n+\n+class TestRequiredArgsAndDefaults:\n+    \"\"\"Acceptance criteria pin the argument names and default values.\"\"\"\n+\n+    @pytest.mark.parametrize(\n+        \"name,expected\",\n+        [\n+            (\"amp\", 0.5),\n+            (\"grain_size_ms\", 80.0),\n+            (\"density\", 12.0),\n+            (\"position\", 0.0),\n+            (\"pitch_transpose_semitones\", 0.0),\n+            (\"pitch_jitter_semitones\", 0.1),\n+            (\"attack_sec\", 0.05),\n+            (\"release_sec\", 0.2),\n+            (\"out_bus\", 0.0),\n+            (\"fx_send\", 0.4),\n+        ],\n+    )\n+    def test_arg_default(\n+        self, scd_source: str, name: str, expected: float\n+    ) -> None:\n+        block = _arg_block(scd_source)\n+        assert _arg_default(block, name) == pytest.approx(expected)\n+\n+    def test_bufnum_arg_present(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        block = _arg_block(scd_source)\n+        # bufnum must be declared so SamplerDispatcher can pass /s_new bufnum N.\n+        assert re.search(r\"\\bbufnum\\s*=\", block), (\n+            \"bufnum arg required so dispatch can target a specific buffer\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_position_rate_arg_present(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        block = _arg_block(scd_source)\n+        assert re.search(r\"\\bposition_rate\\s*=\", block), (\n+            \"position_rate arg required for buffer scrub speed\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_gate_arg_defaults_to_open(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # Sustained voice — gate must default to 1 so the synth runs until\n+        # the dispatcher explicitly closes it via /n_set gate 0.\n+        block = _arg_block(scd_source)\n+        assert _arg_default(block, \"gate\") >= 1.0, (\n+            \"gate must default open (1) so the voice sustains until release\"\n+        )\n+\n+\n+class TestRangeClipping:\n+    \"\"\"Defaults sit inside acceptance ranges; clip() guards keep runtime safe.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_grain_size_clipped_to_acceptance_range(\n+        self, scd_source: str\n+    ) -> None:\n+        # Acceptance range for grain duration is 20..200 ms.\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"grain_size_ms\\.clip\\(\\s*20\\.0\\s*,\\s*200\\.0\\s*\\)\", scd_source\n+        ), \"grain_size_ms must clip to the [20, 200] ms acceptance range\"\n+\n+    def test_density_clipped(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # Density must be positive (Impulse.kr at 0 produces no triggers and\n+        # negative density is undefined) and bounded to keep CPU sane.\n+        assert re.search(r\"density\\.clip\\(\", scd_source), (\n+            \"density must be clipped to a sane positive grains/sec range\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_position_clipped_to_unit_range(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"position\\.clip\\(\\s*0\\.0\\s*,\\s*1\\.0\\s*\\)\", scd_source\n+        ), \"position must clip to the normalized [0, 1] range\"\n+\n+    def test_fx_send_clipped_to_unit_range(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"fx_send\\.clip\\(\\s*0\\.0\\s*,\\s*1\\.0\\s*\\)\", scd_source\n+        ), \"fx_send must clip to [0, 1]\"\n+\n+\n+class TestSignalChain:\n+    \"\"\"All required granular stages must be present in the chain.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_grain_trigger_present(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert \"Impulse.kr\" in scd_source, (\n+            \"granular voice must use Impulse.kr to generate the per-grain \"\n+            \"trigger train at the requested density\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_grainbuf_used_for_buffer_playback(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(r\"GrainBuf\\.ar\\(\", scd_source), (\n+            \"GrainBuf.ar is required for buffered granular synthesis\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_grainbuf_reads_from_bufnum(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # The GrainBuf call must be wired to bufnum (possibly via a local var).\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"GrainBuf\\.ar\\([\\s\\S]*?\\bbufnum\\b\", scd_source\n+        ), \"GrainBuf must read from the bufnum arg\"\n+\n+    def test_pitch_transpose_uses_midiratio(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # Standard SC idiom: convert semitones to a rate multiplier via\n+        # .midiratio so .midiratio(0) == 1.0 (no transposition).\n+        assert \".midiratio\" in scd_source, (\n+            \"pitch_transpose_semitones should drive a .midiratio rate\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_pitch_jitter_uses_per_grain_random(\n+        self, scd_source: str\n+    ) -> None:\n+        # Per-grain randomisation must be re-rolled on each grain trigger,\n+        # which is what TRand.kr (or equivalent) is for.\n+        assert re.search(r\"TRand\\.kr\", scd_source), (\n+            \"pitch jitter must be re-rolled per grain via TRand.kr\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_position_scrub_uses_sweep_or_phasor(\n+        self, scd_source: str\n+    ) -> None:\n+        # Position must advance over time at position_rate; both Sweep.ar and\n+        # Phasor.ar are acceptable phase sources for the scrub.\n+        assert re.search(r\"Sweep\\.ar\", scd_source) or re.search(\n+            r\"Phasor\\.ar\", scd_source\n+        ), (\n+            \"position scrub must integrate position_rate via Sweep.ar/Phasor.ar\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_attack_release_envelope_present(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert \"Env.asr\" in scd_source, (\n+            \"attack/release envelope must use Env.asr for sustained voices\"\n+        )\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"EnvGen\\.kr\\(\\s*Env\\.asr\\([^)]+\\)\\s*,\\s*gate\\b\", scd_source\n+        ), (\n+            \"EnvGen must take the gate arg so gate=0 triggers the release tail\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_envelope_self_frees_with_doneaction_2(\n+        self, scd_source: str\n+    ) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(\n+            r\"EnvGen\\.kr\\([\\s\\S]*?doneAction\\s*:\\s*2\", scd_source\n+        ), (\n+            \"EnvGen must use doneAction: 2 so the synth self-frees once the \"\n+            \"release tail completes\"\n+        )\n+\n+\n+class TestRoutingAndFxSend:\n+    \"\"\"Dry path and parallel fx send must both reach the audio graph.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_dry_writes_to_out_bus(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        assert re.search(r\"Out\\.ar\\(\\s*out_bus\\s*,\", scd_source), (\n+            \"dry signal must be written to out_bus\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_fx_send_writes_to_fx_bus(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # The send must route to the dedicated sw_sampler_fx bus. Either a\n+        # named fx_bus arg or the literal default (16) is acceptable.\n+        assert re.search(r\"Out\\.ar\\(\\s*fx_bus\\s*,\", scd_source) or re.search(\n+            r\"Out\\.ar\\(\\s*16\\s*,\", scd_source\n+        ), \"fx send must write to the sampler effects bus (default 16)\"\n+\n+    def test_fx_bus_default_is_sampler_bus(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        block = _arg_block(scd_source)\n+        # If fx_bus is exposed as an arg, its default must match the global\n+        # sampler-fx bus convention (channels 16/17). If absent, the literal\n+        # 16 in Out.ar is checked above.\n+        match = re.search(r\"\\bfx_bus\\s*=\\s*(\\d+)\", block)\n+        if match is not None:\n+            assert int(match.group(1)) == 16, (\n+                \"fx_bus default must be 16 to match sw_sampler_fx's in_bus\"\n+            )\n+\n+    def test_fx_send_scales_send_only(self, scd_source: str) -> None:\n+        # The dry path must not be multiplied by fx_send (parallel send\n+        # architecture: changing fx_send must not change dry level). We\n+        # check that the Out.ar(out_bus, ...) line does not reference fxAmt.\n+        out_match = re.search(\n+            r\"Out\\.ar\\(\\s*out_bus\\s*,\\s*([^)]+)\\)\", scd_source\n+        )\n+        assert out_match, \"expected an Out.ar(out_bus, ...) call\"\n+        out_arg = out_match.group(1)\n+        assert \"fxAmt\" not in out_arg and \"fx_send\" not in out_arg, (\n+            \"dry write to out_bus must not be scaled by fx_send \"\n+            \"(parallel send architecture)\"\n+        )\n+\n+\n+class TestSCSideTestExists:\n+    \"\"\"The runtime test is the source of truth for the runtime DSP checks.\"\"\"\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_present(self) -> None:\n+        assert SC_TEST_PATH.is_file(), (\n+            f\"SC-side runtime test missing at {SC_TEST_PATH}\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_compiles_source(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        assert \"sw_sampler.scd\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must compile the source SynthDef before loading it\"\n+        )\n+        assert \".load\" in body or \".loadPaths\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must evaluate the source .scd file\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_renders_two_seconds(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        assert re.search(r\"~renderDur\\s*=\\s*2\\.0\", body), (\n+            \"SC-side test must render a 2-second clip per acceptance criteria\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_checks_non_silence(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        assert \"non-silent\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must assert non-silence on the rendered grain cloud\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_checks_spectral_characteristic(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        # Spectral check: the test must run an FFT and inspect bin magnitudes.\n+        assert \".fft(\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must compute an FFT to verify spectral content\"\n+        )\n+        assert \"spectral peak\" in body or \"peakBin\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must locate a spectral peak to verify pitched \"\n+            \"buffer content survives the granular voice\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_exercises_gate_release(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        assert re.search(r\"\\\\gate\\s*,\\s*0\", body), (\n+            \"SC-side test must close the gate (gate=0) to exercise the \"\n+            \"release tail per acceptance criteria\"\n+        )\n+\n+    def test_sc_side_test_uses_known_buffer(self) -> None:\n+        body = SC_TEST_PATH.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n+        # A \"known buffer\" per acceptance criteria: the test must allocate and\n+        # populate one (e.g. with a sine) so the spectral assertion is meaningful.\n+        assert \"Buffer.alloc\" in body, (\n+            \"SC-side test must allocate a buffer to use as the granular source\"\n+        )\n+        assert \"loadCollection\" in body or \"sineFill\" in body or (\n+            \"read\" in body and \".wav\" in body\n+        ), (\n+            \"SC-side test must populate the source buffer with known content \"\n+            \"so spectral assertions have a reference frequency\"\n+        )"}
