{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T05:26:00.341Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777181160147_0","status":"success","output":"# PRD Snapshot - PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument\n**Source:** `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-sampler.md`\n**SHA-256:** `d865ed27e8d12f8b6cda6b42676c6fae756ebc2c1c2c22f4288d7b33bd63b6e7`\n**Captured:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.552156+00:00\n\n---\n# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument\n\n## Overview\n\nCypherClaw's signature palette is a quartet: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`. These are synthesis voices — every sound they make is generated from oscillators, filters, and envelopes. They have no memory of the room, no memory of yesterday, no memory of what just happened. Every piece is born from silence.\n\nThis PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.\n\nThree usages define the artistic intent:\n\n1. **Memory of place.** A continuous rolling buffer of contact + room input. When something is acoustically interesting (a transient cluster, a novel spectral signature, a sustained drone the room produces on its own), the buffer is captured to disk, tagged with the arc phase / mood / time / who-is-in-room, and made available to future scenes. Days later, those moments return — never literally, always granularly transformed — as quiet textures. The room composes itself through CypherClaw.\n\n2. **Self-quotation.** When the composer plays a phrase that scored high on arc payoff, low on click count, and matched intended mood, that phrase is sampled back from `SuperCollider:out_1` and stored under `samples/self/`. Next session, transformed fragments of that phrase return as melodic memory — the Eno tape-loop / Reich phasing aesthetic. The music remembers itself.\n\n3. **Curated found-sound library.** A handpicked `samples/library/` of field recordings, gathered MIDI keyboard captures from Anthony, Theramini phrases, and reference textures. Tagged by character (warm/metallic/wind/pulse/voice/mechanical), pitch, and length. Treated as palette colors, never as sample-pack tropes.\n\nFive principles govern the design:\n\n1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. \"Press button hear sample\" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.\n2. **Memory-tagged, mood-aware selection.** Samples carry rich metadata. The sample-selector matches samples to current artist mode, arc phase, harmonic context, and mood — never random. A sample picked for *Solitary* mode will never appear in *Working ambience* mode unless the metadata aligns.\n3. **Effects-bus parity with the rest of the orchestra.** Sampler output routes through a dedicated effects bus (long delay, convolution reverb, spectral freeze, comb resonance to B fundamental). The effects shape the *character of the voice*, not just gloss on top.\n4. **Self-listening as composition.** The composer's own past output is a primary source. CypherClaw learns from itself.\n5. **Restraint earned, not eroded.** The sampler joins the quartet to make a quintet, but it does not relax the 3-voice base / 2-voice deliberate / 4-voice climax discipline. Heavy sampler use replaces, not adds. In *Solitary* mode the sampler may be the *only* voice.\n\nThe goal is not novelty. It is **continuity**: a listener should feel that the room they're in is being *heard back* through the music, and that today's piece carries echoes of yesterday's.\n\n## Scope and non-goals\n\n**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.\n\n**Out of scope / non-goals:**\n\n- Full DAW-style multi-track sampler with chopping, slicing, or loop-point editing UI. The sampler is a granular voice, not a workstation.\n- ML-based sound classification or auto-tagging from raw audio. Tags come from acoustic-feature heuristics (transient density, spectral centroid, RMS, pitch confidence) — interpretable and debuggable.\n- Replacement of any existing signature voice. The quartet stays; the sampler is added to make a quintet.\n- Real-time pitch-tracking sample triggering from human input. Theramini and keyboard capture are *recorded* into the library and replayed through the granular voice — not used as live MIDI-style triggers.\n- Sample-pack distribution or preset banks. The library is curated by the artist for this room, this installation, this practice.\n- Loudness-matching or mastering of stored samples. Per-sample gain is part of the metadata; the mix engine handles overall balance.\n\n## The five phases\n\n**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.\n\n**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.\n\n**Phase 3 — Live capture daemon (CCS-015..CCS-021).** `sample_capture_daemon.py` maintains rolling 60-second buffers of contact mic + room mic via JACK input; an interesting-moment detector flags acoustically novel windows; flagged windows get saved to `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` with auto-generated tags (arc phase, mood, time, who-is-in-room, acoustic features); systemd unit keeps the daemon running. End of phase: leaving the daemon running for an hour produces ~10–30 tagged WAV files representing the room's acoustic life.\n\n**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.\n\n**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.\n\n## Depends on\n\n- `my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md` — the rendering layer; sampler events flow through the same RenderPass (R-rules respect `role=\"sampler\"` with grid_locked=False so phrasing applies, but R8 microtiming is dampened on grain-time-scale events).\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — Mode-driven voice/tempo/density. `SIGNATURE_VOICES` extends from quartet to quintet; modes specify per-mode sampler density.\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` — `select_cast_ids` already supports `preferred_synths` and `voice_count_target`; the sampler joins the cast through this same path.\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` and `mix_engine.py` — the sampler effects bus routes its summed output through the master, respecting amp/compression caps.\n- Existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/` directory and `boot_synthdefs.scd` — `sw_sampler.scsyndef` joins the boot-time SynthDef load.\n- Live JACK capture path — contact mic on `system:capture_FL` and room mic on `system:capture_FR` (Scarlett inputs already wired via `cypherclaw-jack.service`).\n\n## Key files and modules\n\n- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/sample_library.py` — `SampleRecord` dataclass, `SampleLibrary` (on-disk store + tag index), `SampleSelector` (mood/mode/scene-aware picker)\n- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/synthdefs/sw_sampler.scd` source + compiled `.scsyndef`\n- **New** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd` — dedicated effects bus SynthDef chain\n- **New** `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py` — rolling-buffer + interesting-moment detector + auto-tagger\n- **New** `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` — keeps the daemon alive across reboots\n- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sample_library.py` — selector, tag parsing, mode-aware filtering\n- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` — interesting-moment detector against canned audio\n- **New** `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_integration.py` — end-to-end composer → selector → OSC dispatch\n- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` — `SIGNATURE_VOICES = (..., \"sw_sampler\")`; per-mode `sampler_density` field\n- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/character_registry.py` — `voice_sampler` character with sampler-specific voice metadata\n- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/instrument_patches.py` — patches reference sampler effects-bus presets\n- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/master_bus.py` — sampler-bus mix slot with appropriate gain staging\n- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py` — composer post-piece self-quotation hook + sampler dispatch path\n- **New** `samples/` directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/`:\n  - `library/` — handpicked curated samples (committed metadata only, audio files large)\n  - `self/` — composer self-quotations\n  - `room/` — room-mic captures\n  - `contact/` — contact-mic captures\n  - `theramini/` — Theramini capture phrases\n  - `keyboard/` — MIDI keyboard capture phrases\n  - `index.sqlite` — searchable tag index\n\n## Requirements\n\n| ID | Description | Priority | Tier | Acceptance criteria |\n|----|-------------|----------|------|---------------------|\n| CCS-001 | Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_library.SampleRecord` defined with fields: `sample_id` (UUID), `path` (Path), `source` (Literal['library','self','room','contact','theramini','keyboard']), `character_tags` (frozenset[str]), `pitch_hz` (float \\| None), `pitch_confidence` (float), `duration_sec` (float), `captured_at` (datetime), `arc_phase` (str \\| None), `mood` (dict[str,float] \\| None), `presence` (Literal['present','none','unknown'] \\| None), `rms` (float), `peak` (float), `transient_density` (float), `gain_db` (float, default 0.0)<br/>- dataclass is frozen and JSON-serializable; ISO-8601 timestamp round-trip<br/>- tests verify schema, defaults, JSON round-trip, and rejection of out-of-range values |\n| CCS-002 | Define controlled `CHARACTER_TAGS` vocabulary (warm, metallic, wind, pulse, voice, mechanical, water, sustained, transient, percussive, harmonic, noisy). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_library.CHARACTER_TAGS` is a frozenset of exactly the 12 listed tags<br/>- `SampleRecord.character_tags` validation rejects unknown tags<br/>- tests verify rejection path and the canonical 12-tag set |\n| CCS-003 | Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary(root: Path)` opens / creates `index.sqlite` with table `samples` carrying every `SampleRecord` field plus full-text-search index on `character_tags`<br/>- `library.add(record)` persists row + verifies file presence<br/>- `library.find(source=, character_any=, character_all=, pitch_band=, arc_phase=, mood_range=, limit=)` returns ordered list (most recent first within match set)<br/>- tests cover insert, query by each filter, empty-result path, and corrupted-DB rebuild |\n| CCS-004 | Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary.bootstrap(root)` creates the six subdirectories + `index.sqlite` if missing, idempotent<br/>- documented as the canonical layout in module docstring<br/>- tests verify bootstrap on tmp dir creates all six subdirs and the SQLite file |\n| CCS-005 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord \\| None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |\n| CCS-006 | Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `\"sampler\"` role maps to `\"sw_sampler\"`. | MUST | T1 | - `SIGNATURE_VOICES` becomes `(\"sw_bell_warm\", \"sw_bowed\", \"sw_breath\", \"sw_pad\", \"sw_sampler\")`<br/>- `VOICE_ROLES[\"sampler\"] = \"sw_sampler\"`<br/>- existing `VOICE_ROLES` keys for melody/counter/color/texture/bass unchanged<br/>- existing `test_artist_identity.py::TestSignatureVoices::test_quartet_size` is renamed to `test_quintet_size` and asserts length 5; quartet-specific assertions migrated |\n| CCS-007 | Add `sampler_density` field (0.0–1.0) to `ArtistMode` with mode-specific values: solitary 0.7, companion 0.25, working_ambience 0.10, evening_reflection 0.65, storm 0.45. | MUST | T1 | - `ArtistMode` dataclass gains `sampler_density: float = 0.25` with documentation<br/>- existing five modes updated to the values above<br/>- `apply_mode_to_commission` propagates `sampler_density` into `mode_sampler_density` metadata<br/>- tests verify each mode's value, propagation, and that `sampler_density` is bounded [0.0, 1.0] |\n| CCS-008 | Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = \"sw_sampler\"`, `voice.role = \"sampler\"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. | MUST | T1 | - `character_registry.py` gains `voice_sampler` entry with synth=`sw_sampler`, role=`sampler`, register=`[36, 84]`, params containing default grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose<br/>- character is selectable by `select_cast_ids` when `preferred_synths` includes `sw_sampler`<br/>- tests verify registration and selection through cast planner |\n| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |\n| CCS-010 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |\n| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |\n| CCS-012 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | MUST | T1 | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |\n| CCS-013 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |\n| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |\n| CCS-015 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | MUST | T1 | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |\n| CCS-016 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |\n| CCS-017 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \"warm\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \"metallic\"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → \"sustained\"; transient_density>3/sec → \"percussive\"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → \"harmonic\"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |\n| CCS-018 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |\n| CCS-019 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |\n| CCS-020 | Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. | MUST | T2 | - unit file at `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`<br/>- `User=user`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, `ExecStart=/home/user/cypherclaw/.venv/bin/python3 /home/user/cypherclaw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py`<br/>- `After=cypherclaw-jack.service`, `Requires=cypherclaw-jack.service`<br/>- enabled on boot via `cypherclaw_boot.sh`<br/>- daemon survives a 30-minute soak test with simulated JACK xruns |\n| CCS-021 | Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/fixtures/sample_capture/` directory with WAV fixtures<br/>- `test_sample_capture_daemon.py` exercises each fixture against the detector and asserts expected flag<br/>- fixtures are short (≤2 s) and committed to repo so CI does not need real JACK<br/>- documented as the way to add new detector cases |\n| CCS-022 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | MUST | T1 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |\n| CCS-023 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |\n| CCS-024 | When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. | MUST | T1 | - `sample_capture_daemon.py` listens for keyboard/theramini activity via existing state files (`/tmp/midi_keyboard_activity.json`, `/tmp/theramini_state.json`)<br/>- on >5-second sustained play, captures the corresponding window from the appropriate JACK input<br/>- tags include `human_player` (e.g. `anthony` if face_recognition supports it, else `unknown`), `instrument` (`midi_keyboard` / `theramini`), and the inferred key the human played in<br/>- tests verify trigger threshold, source routing, and tag inclusion |\n| CCS-025 | Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch::transpose_to_key(record, key_name) -> semitones` returns the integer transposition that maps `record.pitch_hz` to the nearest pitch in the current key (B-rooted modes preferred)<br/>- when `record.pitch_confidence < 0.4`, transposition is set to 0 and the sample plays \"atonally\" as a text