transposition, fx_preset, played_at_row}]`, `arc_payoff`, `clicks`<br/>- journal is durable (fsynced after each line)<br/>- tests verify schema and atomicity |\n| CCS-029 | Implement `metrics::sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `metrics::sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` for the metrics-CI gate. | MUST | T1 | - integrated with the existing render `metrics.py` (CCH-014)<br/>- per-piece event count is recorded and surfaced in operator diagnostics<br/>- library:self ratio is computed across the last 50 pieces; healthy band 1.5..3.0<br/>- tests verify metric computation and threshold reporting |\n| CCS-030 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | MUST | T1 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |\n| CCS-031 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | MUST | T1 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |\n| CCS-032 | Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings